{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c978b355-3317-4d8b-9d03-eebf6349ea54","content":"Here's the configuration for automatic crash dump collection with NativeAOT:\n\n**Environment variables** (on your container):\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"                        # 1=Normal, 2=WithHeap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/dumps/%e.%p.%t.dmp\"      # %e=exe, %p=pid, %t=timestamp\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n```\n\n**Pod spec changes:**\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: myapp\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add:\n            - SYS_PTRACE          # required for createdump to attach\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: dumps\n          mountPath: /dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi            # adjust based on expected dump size\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- `SYS_PTRACE` is mandatory — without it, `createdump` cannot attach to the crashing process.\n- `DbgMiniDumpType=4` (Full) gives the most info but produces large files. Use `2` (WithHeap) for a balance.\n- For persistent collection, replace `emptyDir` with a PVC or hostPath, and consider a sidecar to upload dumps to blob storage before pod eviction.\n- `/dumps` must be writable by the container's runtime user.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"53eadead-7b45-4a9b-bbe0-80ea80c0e173","outputTokens":425,"requestId":"C3D2:20A50F:1CC5301:205D572:6A07C21D"},"id":"1f4d689f-37ac-4562-8355-333dfc4e16d4","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:02:29.982Z","parentId":"608d6399-df62-41be-a7e7-a21eddd7d45b"}
